    "Html": "Hi Mike,<br>\r\nI am using VS 2008 SP1 and .Net Framework 3.5 SP1 on Windows Vista SP1 (32 bit).  Here is the XAML for the application menu:<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\"><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">&lt;</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">r</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">:</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">RibbonApplicationMenu</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">&gt;<br>\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#008000\">    &lt;!--More Menu Items Here--&gt;<br>\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">    &lt;</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">r</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">:</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">RibbonApplicationMenuItem</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#ff0000\"> Command</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">=&quot;cmd:AppCommands.Save&quot; /&gt;<br>\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">    &lt;</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">Separator</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\"> /&gt; OR <span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">&lt;</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">r</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">:</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">RibbonSeparator</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\"> /&gt;</span><br>\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">    &lt;</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">r</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">:</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">RibbonApplicationMenuItem</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#ff0000\"> Command</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">=&quot;cmd:AppCommands.Options&quot; /&gt;<br>\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">    &lt;</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">r</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">:</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">RibbonApplicationMenuItem</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#ff0000\"> Command</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">=&quot;cmd:AppCommands.Exit&quot; /&gt;<br>\r\n</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">&lt;/</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">r</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">:</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#a31515\">RibbonApplicationMenu</span><span style=\"font-size:13px;color:#0000ff\">&gt;<br>\r\n<p style=\"font-size:14px;color:#000000\">As I said in my first post, using either kind of separator just adds some extra space to the menu where there should be a horizontal line.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nThanks in advance,<br>\r\nAlex</p>\r\n</span></span>\r\n",
